Should these be tagged with `@[simps]`? I think they need some sort of simp API around them...

Thanks for bringing this up. In my application #17451, only the abstract existence of the natural isomorphism is required, but I agree that it should be possible to look into these definitions (unlike `overEquivPresheafCostructuredArrow` and `CostructuredArrow.toOverCompOverEquivPresheafCostructuredArrow` which should be black boxes). The `simps` lemmas didn't seem particularly great, so I added some API lemmas which look useful when thinking about the results using pen and paper.
